rationale: Improves pipeline performance; unresolved method/design; uses simulation-driven experimentation; relies on computer science/math principles.
Cosmetic UI/branding updates with minor front-end tweaks lack technical uncertainty and a process of experimentation; primarily aesthetic, not improving function/performance.

Aims to improve algorithm performance (permitted purpose), addresses capability/method uncertainty, uses iterative prototyping/testing (process of experimentation), and is grounded in computer science, mathematics, and physics (technological in nature).

Standard ERP–payroll data integration is technological but routine; no technical uncertainty or iterative experimentation demonstrated, and it resembles systems integration/adaptation rather than developing a new or improved software function.

Develops improved sensor calibration techniques (permitted purpose), addresses technical uncertainty, uses simulation and iterative design as experimentation, and relies on engineering/physics principles (technological in nature).
